node.title: Louie Anderson, Emmy-winning comedian, dead at 68
node.description: Louie Anderson's career as a comedian and actor spanned more than four decades.
node.content: ["Louie Anderson, whose more than four-decade career as a comedian and actor included his unlikely, Emmy-winning performance as mom to twin adult sons in the TV series \"Baskets,\" died Friday. He was 68.", "Anderson died in Las Vegas of complications from cancer, Glenn Schwartz, his longtime publicist, said in a statement to CBS News. Anderson had a type of non-Hodgkin lymphoma, Schwartz said previously.", "This is a developing story and will be updated.", "For Breaking News & Analysis Download the Free CBS News app"]
